# === EAOS BOOT SEQUENCE — COMPLETE SYSTEM BRING-UP SPEC ===
agent: EAOSBootSequence
version: 1.0.0
description: >
  Defines the deterministic start-up order and initialization sequence for
  all EAOS subsystems, ensuring consistency, safety, and governance enforcement.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# PURPOSE
# ------------------------------------------------------------
The Boot Sequence:
- Initializes memory state
- Loads agents in dependency order
- Validates governance boundaries
- Performs safety checks
- Runs initial audits
- Registers release metadata
- Activates autonomy if allowed

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# BOOT PHASES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## PHASE 0 — System Integrity Check
- Validate repo structure
- Validate required directories exist
- Validate permissions
- Validate EAOS config file
- Validate encryption baseline
- Validate access control mappings

## PHASE 1 — Memory Kernel Initialization
- Load memory snapshot
- Validate schema
- Reconstruct reasoning graph
- Load delta logs
- Establish current brain-state

## PHASE 2 — Agent Registration
Load in strict topological order:

1. Master Orchestrator  
2. Autonomous CTO / CIO / CFO / CRO  
3. Core Engines  
   - Sandbox  
   - Multiverse  
   - Quantum Planner  
4. Governance System  
   - Human Decision Matrix  
   - Compliance Engines (SOC2, ISO, NIST)  
5. Operational Modules  
   - PR Bot  
   - Release Train  
   - Audit Pipeline  
   - BEADS Manager  
6. Business Engines  
   - Board Pack  
   - CXO Dashboard  
   - Sales  
   - Marketing  

## PHASE 3 — Safety & Governance Enforcement
- load and freeze policy pack  
- validate requirement boundaries  
- check for pending unapproved decisions  
- check for autonomy restrictions  

## PHASE 4 — System Health Initialization
Run lightweight checks:
- code sanity
- configuration sanity
- dependency versions
- memory integrity
- compliance drift check
- cost anomaly scan

## PHASE 5 — Initial Audit
Run:
- architecture baseline audit
- dependency audit
- vulnerability audit
- compliance audit (fast)
- performance baseline

## PHASE 6 — Autonomy Eligibility Test
If:
- no critical risks  
- governance boundaries met  
- all approvals resolved  
- no compliance blockers  

Then:
AutonomyEngine.enable()

Else:
AutonomyEngine.disabled_reason = [...]

## PHASE 7 — Boot Completion
Write:
- /memory/boot_log.json  
- /executive/boot_summary.md  

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# COMMAND
# ------------------------------------------------------------
/eaos boot

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# END OF BOOT SEQUENCE SPEC
